main event: A white egg-shaped object with a red tinge around the edges was observed in DeFuniak Springs, Florida in December 1956. The object was detected on radar and visually observed for 15 to 25 minutes, traveling westward.
interesting points: The object was seen both on ground radar and visually, indicating a multi-witness sighting.
The size of the object kept flashing and out of sight, suggesting possible erratic movement or changing shape.
The sighting involved both civilian and military sources, adding credibility to the report.
There was a discrepancy in the comments about whether the sighting was caused by a helicopter or an error in time estimation, creating uncertainty about the explanation.
The sighting duration of 15 to 25 minutes allowed for a relatively long observation period.
sighted object: white egg-shaped object with a red tinge
